## Description {#details}

This file declares a class that exposes a simple in-memory representation of a document of MsgPack objects, that can be read from MsgPack, written to MsgPack, and inspected and modified in memory.

This is intended to be a lighter-weight (in terms of memory allocations) replacement for MsgPackTypes.

<Link id="l00404" /><CodeLine lineNumber="404"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Read a document from a binary msgpack blob, merging into anything already</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00405" /><CodeLine lineNumber="405"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// in the Document. The blob data must remain valid for the lifetime of this</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00406" /><CodeLine lineNumber="406"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Document (because a string object in the document contains a StringRef</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00407" /><CodeLine lineNumber="407"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// into the original blob). If Multi, then this sets root to an array and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00408" /><CodeLine lineNumber="408"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// adds top-level objects to it. If !Multi, then it only reads a single</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00409" /><CodeLine lineNumber="409"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// top-level object, even if there are more, and sets root to that. Returns</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00410" /><CodeLine lineNumber="410"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// false if failed due to illegal format or merge error.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00411" /><CodeLine lineNumber="411"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00412" /><CodeLine lineNumber="412"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// The Merger arg is a callback function that is called when the merge has a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00413" /><CodeLine lineNumber="413"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// conflict, that is, it is trying to set an item that is already set. If the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00414" /><CodeLine lineNumber="414"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// conflict cannot be resolved, the callback function returns -1 If the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00415" /><CodeLine lineNumber="415"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// conflict can be resolved, the callback returns a non-negative number and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00416" /><CodeLine lineNumber="416"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// sets &#42;DestNode to the resolved node. The returned non-negative number is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00417" /><CodeLine lineNumber="417"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// significant only for an array node; it is then the array index to start</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00418" /><CodeLine lineNumber="418"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// populating at. That allows Merger to choose whether to merge array</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00419" /><CodeLine lineNumber="419"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// elements (returns 0) or append new elements (returns existing size).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00420" /><CodeLine lineNumber="420"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00421" /><CodeLine lineNumber="421"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// If SrcNode is an array or map, the resolution must be that &#42;DestNode is an</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00422" /><CodeLine lineNumber="422"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// array or map respectively, although it could be the array or map</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00423" /><CodeLine lineNumber="423"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// (respectively) that was already there. MapKey is the key if &#42;DestNode is a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00424" /><CodeLine lineNumber="424"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// map entry, a nil node otherwise.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00425" /><CodeLine lineNumber="425"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00426" /><CodeLine lineNumber="426"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// The default for Merger is to disallow any conflict.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00427" /><CodeLine lineNumber="427"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">bool</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/msgpack/document/#aa1132fee67332a4c0a707984b97f9b52">readFromBlob</a>(</span></CodeLine>
